 914:				; HL - points to first character after options and any trailing spaces.
 915:				; C flag - set on error (malformed option string)
 916:				; Each bit in A corresponds to one character in the options list. Bit 0 is set
 917:				; of the first character is encountered, bit 1 for the second and so on. Options
 918:				; may begin with "[", "/" or "$", to match all conventions I have found used
 919:				; with CP/M. If no options are included in the command line, A will be set to
 920:				; zero (no options set). Option characters may include any printable character
 921:				; except space or "]". Lower case is not permitted. Duplicates are ignored.
